metadata.name: Unsolicited abstraction of modern times #174
metadata.description:
This piece is an abstraction and a reflection on the last era, on all that we have built and become. Are we proud of it or has it just been the result of iterating through the days? Since the technology boom, we have experienced great improvements, but perhaps also massive ...mistakes?‚Ä®‚Ä®

Inspired by textbooks of the 80s, with elements that remind us of industry, technology, networks and systems, "Unsolicited abstraction of modern times" invites us to question our work to date. Has everything really changed?

unknowable 2022




Usage:
press [s] - save pixels (png)
press [p] - save vectors (svg)

metadata.name: Copenhagen Interpretation #34
metadata.description:
The Copenhagen Interpretation of quantum physics suggests that objects don't have physical properties until being observed.

In this generative piece by itsgalo and Sp√∏gelsesmaskinen, a set of objects are being held in "superposition" and finally positioned when observed and minted.

Use mouse/touch to zoom, pan, and rotate. Press 's' to grab a screenshot. Best viewed in Firefox.

metadata.name: contrapuntos #125
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #405
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Sunset on Water #45
metadata.description:
Third iteration of my Sumi-e inspired pieces.

This time featuring a sun setting over the ocean, seen through bamboo sprouts and some birds up in the air.

Placement and size of the sun as well as light differences in its colouring are determined by the hash. The bamboo will be fairly evenly distributed across the width of the image, but the size, off-sprouts and leafs are also randomised and will create a unique image every time.

Everything is generated programmatically. Implemented in Vanilla Javascript.

metadata.name: Outside your Window #64
metadata.description:
Never take for granted that we sit in the safety of our homes, behind our windows, sheltered from the elements outside. 

The characteristics of the rain outside the window, and the window itself, will be determined by the mint hash. However, the background color of this piece will constantly change based on the hour of day it is loaded, hence note that the thumbnail will only technically be accurate 1/24 hours out of the day as it represents a static snapshot taken at the time of token rendering.

100% of the primary proceeds will be donated towards flood relief efforts for the devastating December 2021 floods in Malaysia.

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid
